1)Array reverse Program using for loop
package com.info.windows;

public class Reverse 
{
	public static void main(String args[])
	{
		int arr[]= {1,2,3,4};
		for(int i=arr.length-1;i>=0;i--)
		{
			System.out.println(arr[i]);
		}
	}

}
output :4 3 2 1

2)Take size from user and take value from user and print
package com.info.windows;
import java.util.*;
public class Reverse 
{
	public static void main(String args[])
	{

			Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
			System.out.println("Enter thr required of size");
			int size=sc.nextInt();
			int arr[]=new int[size];
			System.out.println("Enter the element one by one");
			for(int i=0;i<size;i++)
			{
				arr[i]=sc.nextInt();
			}
			System.out.println(Arrays.toString(arr));		
	}
	
}

output:
Enter thr required of size
4
Enter the element one by one
9
3
2
1
[9, 3, 2, 1]

